br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Take a second look at this.</span><hr size=1> do you even realize the damage potential on this spell line? Think about it. 3 melees in a group, hitting what 2 times a second each? 5 point offensive shield would be 30 dps on top of whatever else we can do. at 2k mana, I could fire it off twice, making 60 dps, med to full, 2 more gropus, 120 DPS ... that's sustained, and I can still nuke inbetween those recasts.<br>
<br>
Problem with any of those improvements, Fizzi, they ALL make us better at soloing. So does that yalp spell. The only way we can get better at grouping / raiding is spells we just can't use soloing. That means long cast time nukes -- which wold be largely useless on raids unless it's a boss mob. <p><image src=http://www.webhazard.net/images/Vote-Sig/ennya_kiel.jpg><BR>
Sorceress, Master Slayer, WurmSlayer, 
WurmHunter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akaryn>Akaryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/15/02 2:22:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=799.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> The wizard class is broken. The words in this topic clearly show that I am not the only one that believes it to be so. With the introduction of PoP and to a lesser extent Luclin our usefulness has dramatically declined. Our translocation and porting ability no longer competes with druids alone. But this is only the smallest of problems I have begun to see. Recently I have had the opportunity to raid and have found that the wizard class is not a vital aspect of any raid I have been on. Sure, we throw out a lot of damage but to avoid aggro we have to wait and generally get off one nuke, maybe two before the mob is defeated. Only on bosses  can we fulfill our full potential of damage. We should have options instead of sitting and waiting for the 40% of health to drop. I love the idea of adding dam to the main tanks but is it enough to make wizards a viable choice versus other caster classes?  No, I dont want to be best choice just a viable one for raids and when groups are looking for more. Instead of telling you what I dont want let me throw some brainstorming your way and see what more knowledgeable people think. <br>
<br>
A nuke spell cast upon the main tank that is held until the tank first hits the target and is unleashed upon the target.  Aggro of spell stays upon tank. I know, sounds like a breach of eq law, but it is certainly inline with giving the wizard more group, and raid viability. This would allow increased aggo on main tank and allow more to join the fray earlier. The casting time could be enormous to ensure that it used only once per mob, perhaps only once per two mobs. <br>
<br>
A mini evac spell that pulls one target to location of caster and removes aggro from that individual. This could be abused so its mana cost, recast time or casting distance should reflect this, however it should have a fast cast time or it becomes near worthless in saving a party member.   This could be invaluable if one member of the party pulls more than the party can handle. Perhaps a simpler version of this would only reduce the amount of aggro the target currently has. This would be similar to the concussion spell, but for group or raid members. <br>
<br>
The ability to channel mana to another caster. This sounds counter productive to the wizard, but I am talking about group and raid viability and am interested in aiding the party as a whole. Sometimes you wish the (insert caster class here) had one more spell to give. No, I dont want to be a mana pool for the other casters, there needs to limits imposed so it is used only in emergencies. <br>
<br>
Well, its 2 am and my brain is mush, that is all I can come up with on the fly but will put much more thought into it and get back to you. If any of these reflect spells of other casters it is unintentional, I am, always have been, and always will be a wizard. My knowledge of other casters is incomplete and their spell lists vast.  But what is certain, when raids or groups are forming I want to hear, We could really use a wizard as opposed to Okay, we will take you if we cant get a (insert any other caster class here).<br>
<br>
<br>
